Balanced Budget and Ministerial Accountability Act
Minister of State for Community Safety and Integrated Services
Expected Results for the 2025-2026 Fiscal Year Regulation
Application of this regulation
1  This regulation applies to the Minister of State for Community Safety and Integrated Services for the 2025/2026 fiscal year.

Definition
2  In this regulation, "Act" means the Balanced Budget and Ministerial Accountability Act.

Minister of State for Community Safety and Integrated Services
3  The expected results that the Minister of State for Community Safety and Integrated Services is to achieve for the purposes of section 5 (3) of the Act are as follows:

(a)continue to engage with local governments, community associations and the Province's business community to discuss issues relating to the incidence of street disorder in the Province;

(b)continue to support ministries and stakeholders in the development of strategies to mitigate the impact of street disorder on local governments, community associations and the Province's business community;

(c)make progress in carrying out the commitments identified in the mandate letter of the Minister of State for Community Safety and Integrated Services;

(d)submit a report to Cabinet on the results referred to in paragraphs (a) to (c) on or before March 31, 2026.

[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: Balanced Budget and Ministerial Accountability Act, S.B.C. 2001, c. 28, s. 9.]

